description: This table contains all the Patient Order Template (OTP) items related to medication doses that are initially calculated by a dose suggestion programming point and are later overridden by a user.

columns.name: PP_OVRD_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description:
Reason for entering a dose that is significantly different from the formula calculated dose.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 No Entries Defined

columns.name: PP_OVRD_USER_ID
columns.description: The user who is overriding the dose change warning.

columns.name: PP_OVRD_DTTM
columns.description: The instant at which the dose change override reason was entered.

columns.name: PP_OVRD_AUTH_PR_ID
columns.description: The provider who authorized the override reason that was entered during release.

columns.name: FORM_DESC_AT_ORDER
columns.description: The formula description at the time that the dose was entered.

columns.name: FORM_CALC_DOSE_AT_O
columns.description: The dose that the formula suggested to the user at the time that the dose was entered.

columns.name: FORM_UNIT_AT_ORDR_C_NAME
columns.description:
The dose units that the formula suggested to the user at the time that the dose was entered.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes
